rComments: I found the course very interesting.  I think its important to remember that this was just a survey course, so the point in broad knowledge rather than really in depth analysis.  I thought the marking on the exam was a little harsh given how easily the midterm and the essay were marked

Contrary to the previous commentators, I found Smick's lectures to be pretty helpful in that she summarizes the key points after explaining major themes or concepts, making everything clear. She doesn't go on that many tangents (unlike Wollesen), and when she does they only help enrich your understanding of the concept.

very poor organization,no defined purpose in each class, she just shows up a bunch of slides and talks on each with no connection to a theme or the next slide.she cares more about crazy listings of words and Latin expressions and historical events than the works of art. DO NOT TAKE COURSE WITH HER! it is more of a history-mixed-with-Latin course.

She can be somewhat dry, but she's not as bad as the previous comment makes her out to be. She digresses a lot, but the digressions are meaningful if you keep in mind the themes she stresses. She seems a little unorganized but generally easy to approach.

Does not stick to the subject matter whatsoever. Will discuss things for 20 minutes which have no apparent relevence, as they are not mentioned in tutorial or in the text. Tells us that we don't have to worry about certain topics, then they will appear on the exam. Is so mind-numbingly boring that you can't help but fall asleep.
